      <h2>How to make Microwavable Oatmeal </h2>
        <p>Take your microwavable bowl and place 1 cup of oats. You will add of your choice milk or water. Add 1/2 cup or until oats are somewhat over the liquid. Take your bowl and place in microwave on high setting for 1 minute and 30 seconds. Take bowl out and add your chocolate chips and a dash of cinnamon for flavor. A simple ingredient made within 3 minutes.</p>
        <p>Ingredients — 3 eggs, salt, pepper, 1/2 cup vegetables, 1 serving of cheese, cooking spray. Time elapsed - 15 minutes // Time prep - 5 minutes </p>
