      <h2>How to make Overnight oats </h2>
        <p>This recipe is for those who do not have time to cook. One of my favorites. Get a bottle or small mason jar and place one cup of oats. Then add your chia seeds after and add nut butter of choice. If you’d like, you can add a **protein powder for the extra boost. Add your milk and close the container. Give it a shake and let it sit overnight.</p>
        <p>Ingredients — bottle or mason jar, 1 cup of oats, 15g of chia seeds, 18g of almond or peanut butter, **1/2 scoop of protein powder (optional), 1/2 cup of milk. Time elapsed - 5 minutes // Time prep - 3 minute.</p>
